## Read first
All real documentation lives in **`DOCS/`** — keep it current as you work.
- **`DOCS/README.md`** — doc index + maintenance rules.
- **`DOCS/ARCHITECTURE.md`** *(agent)* — structure, hard rules, invariants, conventions, data flow,
  storage, known quirks, build/run/test. **Start here.**
- **`DOCS/MODULE_MAP.md`** *(agent)* — per-file public API; work without reading every source file.
- **`DOCS/USER_MANUAL.md`** *(human)* — domain concepts and end-user behavior.
- **`DOCS/CHANGELOG.md`** — what changed (newest first).
- **`DOCS/ROADMAP.md`** — planned features + who is working on what (claim before you start).
- **`DOCS/archive/`** — original design notes + archived changelog history.

